definition.value: A disaccharide comprising 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranose (Kdo) having a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranosyl (Kdo-CH2OH) residue attached at the 4-position.
The cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is ferroheme c protonated to pH 7.3.
A phosphocholine that is the 4-aminophenyl ester of choline phosphate.
The cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is bacteriochlorophyll a protonated to pH 7.3.
The cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is chlorophyll b protonated to pH 7.3.
An enal consisting of pent-2-ene having an oxo group at the 1-position
Pantetheine 4'-phosphate(2-) with D (R) configuration at the 2' position. The dianion formed from D-pantetheine 4'-phosphate by deprotonation of the phosphate group; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An enal consisting of hept-2-ene having an oxo group at the 1-position.
An enal consisting of oct-2-ene having an oxo group at the 1-position.
An enal consisting of non-2-ene having an oxo group at the 1-position.
A decenal in which the C=C bond is located at the 2-3 position.
An aldehyde in which the carbon alpha to the carbonyl group is part of a hydroxypolyether system.
An organic phosphate in which one of the terminal hydroxy groups of an alpha,alpha-dihydroxypolyether is phosphorylated.

A sialodiosylceramide consisting of the tetrasaccharide 9-O-acetyl-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose attached glycosidically to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide.
The 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion that is 5-methyl-dCTP protonated to pH 7.3.

A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of the hexasaccharide beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide.

A sialotetraosylceramide consisting of a linear pentasaccharide made up from one sialyl residue, two galactose residues, one N-acetylgalactosamine residue and a glucose residue at the reducing end attached to the ceramide portion via a beta-linkage.
The lipid oxoanion formed from lipid IIA by deprotonation of the phosphate hydroxy groups.
A lipid A derivative in which the phospho group at the anomeric carbon is esterified with a 4-amino-4-deoxy-beta-L-arabinopyranosyl group.
A carbotricyclic compound that is cis-1,1a,4,4a,5,6,7,8-octahydrocyclopropa[d]naphthalene which is substituted by methyl groups at the 2, 4a, 8 and 8 positions.
A thujopsene that has (R,R,R)-configuration.

An amino trisaccharide consisting of beta-L-rhamnose at the reducing end having a 4,6-O-[(1S)-1-carboxyethylidene]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-alpha-D-galactosyl group attached at the 4-position.
A cyclodepsipeptide antibiotic, which is isolated from the filamentous fungus Aureobasidium pullulans R106 and is toxic to yeast at low concentrations (0.1-0.5 ug/ml).
A linear tetrasaccharide consisting of four alpha-L-rhamnose units joined by sequential (1->2)-, (1->3)- and (1->2)-linkages.
An amino disaccharide consisting of alpha-L-rhamnose having an N-acetyl beta-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at the 2-position.
A glycosylmannose consisting of an beta-D-galactofuranosyl residue attached to alpha-D-mannopyranose at the 3-position.
A glycosylmannose consisting of an beta-D-galactofuranosyl residue attached to alpha-D-mannopyranose at the 6-position.
A carbobicyclic compound and sesquiterpene that is spiro[5.5]undec-2-ene which is substituted by a methylidene group at position 11 and by methyl groups at positions 3, 7 and 7.
A 4,6-O-[(1R)-1-carboxyethylidene]-D-galactose having beta-configuration at the anomeric centre.
The (6S)-enantiomer of beta-chamigrene.
A monosaccharide derivative consisting of D-galactose having a 1-carboxyethylidene group masking the 4-and 6-positions.
The (E)-isomer of oct-2-enal.
A triterpene glycoside and hemiacetal isolated from a fermentation of Hormonema sp. and which specifically inhibits glucan synthesis in fungal cells.
A carbohydrate derivative consisting of beta-D-galactose having a 1-carboxyethylidene group masking the 3-and 4-positions.
A member of the class of phenylacetic acids that is phenylacetic acid having a (2,6-dichlorophenyl)amino group at the 2-position and a 2-(2-oxoethoxy)ethoxy group at the 5-position.
A sialopentaosylceramide having beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialopentaosyl component.
A branched glycoside consiting of propyl alpha-L-rhamnoside having alpha-L-rhamnosyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residues at the 2- and 2-positions respectively.
A lipid A comprising lipid IVA glycosylated with two 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonic acid (KDO) residues and carrying an additional 4-amino-4-deoxy-beta-L-arabinopyranosyl esterifying group.
The organophosphate oxoanion formed from beta-L-Ara4N-(KDO)2-lipid IVA by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucose at the reducing end having an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 4-position.
A trideoxyhexose comprising D-galactopyranose having the hydroxy groups at positions 2- and 4- replaced by acetamido and amino groups respectively and also deoxygenated at the 6-position.
A polyprenyl glycosyl phosphate in which the glycosyl moiety is D-mannosyl and the polyprenyl group is di-trans,poly-cis-undecaprenyl.
The organophosphate oxoanion formed by deprotonation of the phosphate OH in D-mannosyl ditrans,polycis-undecaprenyl phosphate. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A glucotriose consisting of three D-glucose units joined by beta-(1->2)-linkages
A linear trisaccharide consisting of three L-rhamose units joined by alpha-(1->2)-linkages
A linear amino tetrasaccharide composed of alpha-L-rhamnose, alpha-D-galactose, N-acetyl beta-D-glucosamine and alpha-L-rhamnose units joined by sequential (1->3)-, (1->3)- and (1->4)-linkages.
A galactotriose composed of three beta-D-galactose units joined by (1->6)-linkages.
A 2'-deoxycytidine phosphate having 5-methylcytosine as the nucleobase.
A pentasaccharide derivative composed of a 4-O-methyl-beta-D-glucuronic acid (at the non-reducing end) and four beta-D-galactose units all joined via (1->6)-linkages.
